fix: remove spinner flicker on route navigation with DelayedFallback

One file changed: src/App.tsx

The global <Suspense> wrapping all lazy routes had fallback={<PageLoader />}.
On every client-side navigation React unmounted the incoming lazy chunk,
suspended, and immediately rendered the full-page spinner — even for chunks
that were already cached and resolved in < 1 frame. This caused the visible
flash: spinner → skeleton → content.

Fix: replace <PageLoader /> in the fallback with <DelayedFallback />.
DelayedFallback renders nothing for the first 150 ms. If the lazy chunk
resolves within that window (true for any already-cached chunk and most
fast-network loads) the user sees nothing at all — the skeleton the page
renders on its own appears directly. Only if the chunk genuinely takes
longer than 150 ms does the spinner appear, which is the correct behavior
for slow connections or first-load of an uncached chunk.

useState and useEffect were added to the React import; no other changes.
